# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an app, you may or may not want to ignore it.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're executing Pipenv in a virtualenv, it might create a directory there.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock should be tracked, but virtualenvs inside the project should be ignored.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, pdm.lock should be tracked, but .pdm-python and __pypackages__ should be ignored.
.pdm-python
__pypackages__/

